dct_description_sm: New Jersey. Department of Conservation and Economic Development. Division of Planning and Development. Atlas Sheet 26 (1955) New Jersey Geological Survey. Alternte title: [New Jersey.] Atlas sheet 26. Relief shown by 10 feet contour interval and spot heights. Depth shown by soundings in feet at low tide. Title was not given. Region covered: vicinity of Newark and Jersey City. Original survey made under the direction of C. C. Vermeule, Topographer in 1880-3, 1955 revision by R. G. Blanchard, Topographic Engineer.
dct_publisher_sm: Trenton, N.J. : New Jersey Geological Survey, 1955.
